    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Columns so shaped as to present a twisted or spiral form. The form was an eastern motif, adopted in Byzantine architecture and decoration. It was believed that such columns were used in Solomon's temple.</Note_Text>
